<paragraph blockId="10.[189,896,811,874]" box="[234,466,811,838]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,812,838]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[313,409,812,838]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1812,1838]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,265,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[289,1297,265,1777]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Adult habitus, ♂, dorsal view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. falsus Becker, 1922, Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). E. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). F. E. jacobsoni Becker, 1913, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). G. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, abdomen, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). H. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239303/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">Figs 3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[422,457,811,838]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1814,1840]" captionTargetBox="[290,1294,268,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[290,1294,268,1774]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Adult habitus, ♂, lateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. falsus Becker, 1922, Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). E. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). F. E. jacobsoni Becker, 1913, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). G. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). H. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239319/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">6B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,896,811,874]" box="[189,896,847,874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">
MEASUREMENTS. Body length: 
<quantity box="[539,632,847,873]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="7.8">7.8 mm</quantity>
; wing length: 
<quantity box="[799,892,847,874]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="116" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,912,1290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">
HEAD (
<figureCitation box="[269,350,912,938]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[189,232,1846,1872]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,511,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-56@25.[189,1399,511,1807]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 13. Head, ♂, dorsal view (A, C, E, G, I) and lateral view (B, D, F, H). A–B. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C–D. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). E–F. E. falsus Becker, 1922, Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). G–H. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). I. E. tricolor (Fabricius, 1798), Paleochori, Greece (JSA). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239359/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
C–D). Eyes short and white pilose, dichoptic, 2–3 ommatidia spaced; face nearly parallelsided, weakly grey pollinose, with whitish pile; frontal triangle weakly grey pollinose, entirely covered with dense and long white pile; head in frontal view 3.2 times as wide as face; frontal triangle almost 1.3 times as long as vertical triangle; vertical triangle almost entirely shiny black, with yellowish pile; ocellar triangle nearly equilateral; ocellar triangle bulging and shiny black, with black pile, about as long as vertical triangle; distance between posterior ocelli to posterior margin of eye nearly 0.8 times as long as ocellar triangle; occiput light grey pollinose, with light pile; frontal triangle nearly 1.6 times as wide as ocellar triangle; vertex at posterior corner of eyes 1.15 times as wide as vertex over posterior ocelli; head in dorsal view 4.5 times as wide as vertex at posterior corner of eyes; scape brown; pedicel yellowish brown; basoflagellomere orange, 1.2 times as long as wide; arista brown, 1.3 times as long as basoflagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[405,512,1264,1290]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[186,229,1739,1765]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,317,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-18@21.[188,1398,317,1686]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Basoflagellomere, mediolateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). C. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). E. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, ♂, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). F. E. hissaricus Stackelberg, 1949, ♂, Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). G. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). H. E. pilosipedes Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). I. E. vallicolus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: a = length of basoflagellomere; b = width of basoflagellomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239347/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1398,1330,1496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">THORAX. Scutum and scutellum shiny black with very short yellowish pile; scutum with two narrow median pollinose vittae reaching to median suture; anterior part of median vittae semi-triangular; posterolateral part of scutum with a longitudinal row of black setulae above base of wing; scutellum with marginal rim; pleurae shiny black; anepisternum, katepisternum and anepimeron covered with short yellowish pile.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,1536,1703]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">
LEGS (
<figureCitation box="[272,374,1536,1562]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1849,1875]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,315,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[189,1399,315,1764]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 9. Metaleg, lateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). C. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). E. E. hissaricus Stackelberg, 1949, ♂, Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). F. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239337/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Legs shiny black, with yellowish short pile; procoxa orange apically; femora predominantly black except for orange apical tip and basal narrow orange margin, basal half and apex of tibiae orange; tarsi mostly orange except for brownish-black dorsally; metafemur simple, slightly enlarged, about 3 times as long as wide, with very short yellowish pile ventrally; anteroventral and posteroventral margins of metafemur each with a row of 8 respectively 5 black setae in about apical half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1343,1742,1775]" box="[189,1343,1742,1775]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">
WING. Entirely microtrichose; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[624,651,1761,1775]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">4+5</subScript>
nearly straight; calypters whitish; halter yellowish-orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,1807,1939]" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">
ABDOMEN. Black, covered with very short yellowish pile except for long whitish pile on tergum II anterolaterally; terga II–IV each with a pair of lunulate-shaped oblique maculae of white pollinosity; sterna brown, with yellowish short pile; sternum IV rectangular, with rounded posterolateral corners and with median wide V-shaped incision posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[766,874,1913,1939]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,232,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,306,1755]" captionTargetId="figure-19@23.[189,1399,306,1755]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Sternum IV, ♂, ventral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). D. E. hissaricus Stackelberg, 1949, Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). E. E. pilosipedes Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). F. E. vallicolus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239351/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="116">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1398,265,397]" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">
GENITALIA (
<figureCitation box="[324,435,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="31.[189,232,1850,1876]" captionTargetBox="[301,1285,286,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-18@31.[298,1289,263,1811]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Fig. 18. Epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). D. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). E. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). F. E. richteri Stackelberg, 1960, Lar, Iran (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239387/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">Figs 18B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[452,501,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="35.[189,232,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[306,1283,308,1705]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[300,1288,265,1809]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="Fig. 20. Right surstylus, dorsal view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis. sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). D. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). E. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). F. E. richteri Stackelberg, 1960, Lar, Iran (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239395" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239395/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">20B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[518,568,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1847,1873]" captionTargetBox="[213,1377,308,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-18@37.[205,1381,265,1808]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 22. Hypandrium, lateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). C. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). D. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Chekab Valley, Iran (HMIM). E. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype (HMIM). F. E. richteri Stackelberg, 1960, Lar, Iran (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239401/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">22B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium simple; aedeagal apodeme in lateral view narrow and abruptly bent apically; cercus semi-rectangular; posterior lobe of surstylus in lateral view thumb-shaped apically and in dorsal view uniformly rounded apically and entirely covered with short setulae dorsally; inner accessory lobe of surstylus with short pile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,436,673]" box="[234,707,436,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,325,436,462]" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[341,439,436,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1916,1942]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,836,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-149@9.[189,1398,836,1873]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Adult habitus, ♀, dorsal view. A. Eumerus brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype (HMIM). B. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). C. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Mian Jangal, Iran (JSA). D. E. persarum Stackelberg, 1961, Bazman, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239315" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239315/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">Figs 5A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[451,489,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1812,1838]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,336,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[189,1399,336,1746]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 8. A–E. Adult habitus, lateral view. F. Basicosta. A–D. Female. E–F. Male. A. Eumerus brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype (HMIM). B. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). C. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Mian Jangal, Iran (JSA). D. E. persarum Stackelberg, 1961, Bazman, Iran (JSA). E. E. tricolor (Fabricius, 1798), Paleochori, Greece (JSA). F. E. tadzhikorum Stackelberg, 1949, Chekab Valley, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ac = anterodorsal costal setae; pc = posterodorsal costal setae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239333/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">8A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[502,538,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1849,1875]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,315,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-19@17.[189,1399,315,1764]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 9. Metaleg, lateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). C. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). E. E. hissaricus Stackelberg, 1949, ♂, Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). F. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239337/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">9C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[550,601,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[186,229,1739,1765]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,317,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-18@21.[188,1398,317,1686]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Basoflagellomere, mediolateral view. A. Eumerus atricolorus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). B. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). C. E. brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (HMIM). D. E. chekabicus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). E. E. kazanovzkyae Paramonov, 1927, ♂, Paveh, Iran (HMIM). F. E. hissaricus Stackelberg, 1949, ♂, Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). G. E. ovoformus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). H. E. pilosipedes Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). I. E. vallicolus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (HMIM). Scale bars = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: a = length of basoflagellomere; b = width of basoflagellomere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239347/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">11C</figureCitation>
