<figureCitation box="[613,641,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,597,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-82@26.[189,1399,596,1846]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 14. Head, ♀, dorsal view (A, C, E, G) and lateral view (B, D, F, H). A–B. Eumerus brevipilosus Gilasian &amp; van Steenis sp. nov., paratype (HMIM). C–D. E. coeruleus (Becker, 1913), Ghoochan, Iran (HMIM). E–F. E. longitarsis Peck, 1979, Mian Jangal, Iran (JSA). G–H. E. persarum Stackelberg, 1961, Bazman, Iran (JSA). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4239361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4239361/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">14</figureCitation>
A–B)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,436,673]" pageId="11" pageNumber="117">
Body length: 
<quantity box="[351,496,471,498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="8.2" metricValueMin="7.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="8.0" valueMax="8.2" valueMin="7.8">7.8–8.2 mm</quantity>
; wing length: 6.0– 
<quantity box="[718,811,471,498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="117" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
. Same as male except for sexual dimorphism and for the following characters: frons shiny black, weakly pollinose laterally and with short yellowish pile; vertex at posterior corner of eyes as wide as vertex over posterior ocelli; head in dorsal view 4 times as wide as vertex at posterior corner of eyes; scutum with median narrow pollinose vittae reaching to ⅓ behind median suture; anepisternum, katepisternum and anepimeron covered with very short yellowish pile.
</paragraph>
